gujarati.context:
The monk died three days without food; 
They went away at dawn, without having eaten, at sunrise;
They crossed the river, where people cried out for bread, 
At the time when one has not eaten, in the morning.

Here is the translation:

After becoming a monk, he has become homeless, wandering from place to place in sorrow; 
Above, my mind is full of grief, do not take it with you when you leave from here, O child.

Here is the translation:

He says Muniswami's are there, far away, having gone left and right;
He has spoken wisely, O sage, go to your guru and ask for wealth.

I am not one, I do not reside here; 
The whirlwind of Panchaali's lament is mine;
But guru has taken me away, I have come to this place without a glance.
